Getafe would like to sign Real Madrid's Brahim Diaz on loan this summer, president Angel Torres has confirmed.<br />
<br />
&quot;Real Madrid know we're interested in him,&quot; Torres told Cadena COPE radio after Getafe's Europa League defeat to Inter on Wednesday. &quot;If they let us and he wants to come, we'll make room for him at Getafe.&quot;

Benfica coach Jorge Jesus says his club is doing all it can to sign highly-coveted forward Edinson Cavani.<br />
<br />
&quot;Cavani is a player that has various offers on the market and he is thinking about his options,&quot; Jesus, hired last month from Brazilian giants Flamengo, told reporters. &quot;If you ask me do I want him? Who wouldn't want him? Not just for Benfica but for Portuguese football. We know it's not easy financially. The president is doing all they can for it to happen.&quot;

